South Africa's flanker Siya Kolisi (C) lifts the Webb Ellis Cup as they celebrate winning the Japan 2019 Rugby World Cup final match between England and South Africa at the International Stadium Yokohama in Yokohama on November 2, 2019. JOHANNESBURG - The Springboks are on their way home after bagging even more accolades in Japan. The public will be able to celebrate their victory later this week. Coach Rassie Erasmus, captain Siya Kolisi and vice-captain Handre Pollard are expected to arrive in the country on Tuesday afternoon at 4.30pm. The rest of the squad will arrive in South Africa on Wednesday. The Rugby World Cup Champions Tour kicks off on Thursday with a parade in Pretoria, Johannesburg and Soweto. 